# Agenda table structure (memory bank)

All agenda tables in this project follow this convention.

## Title above the table

- **Format:** `The agenda: [start day] to [end day] [Month] [Year]`
- **Examples:** `The agenda: 21 to 23 April 2026`, `The agenda: 8 to 10 June 2017`
- Use as heading (e.g. `## The agenda: 21 to 23 April 2026`) directly above the table.

## Required columns

| Column | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Date** | Session date(s), e.g. `8–10 June 2017` or `Tuesday 21 April 2026` |
| **Speaker** | Speaker name(s) |
| **Topic** | Session title or topic |

## Optional columns

### Time (2nd column)

- **When:** Only if exact times are available.
- **Header:** Use an empty header (e.g. `| Date | | Speaker | Topic |`) so the 2nd column holds times such as `09:00 - 10:00`.
- **Omit** if times are not known or not applicable.

### Resources (final column)

- **When:** Only after the summit, if video, slides, or other materials exist.
- **Header:** `Resources`
- **Content:** Links, e.g. `[YouTube](url)`, `[Slides](url)`.
- **Omit** for upcoming or past summits with no resources yet.

## Column order

1. Date  
2. (optional) Time  
3. Speaker  
4. Topic  
5. (optional) Resources  

## Examples

**Minimal (before summit, no times):**
```
| Date | Speaker | Topic |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 8–10 June 2017 | Sami Laiho | How to effectively build video-based learning material |
```

**With times, no resources:**
```
| Date | | Speaker | Topic |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Tuesday 21 April 2026 | 09:00 - 10:00 | Jasmin Kahriman | Opening Session |
```

**Full (after summit, with times and resources):**
```
| Date | | Speaker | Topic | Resources |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Tuesday 21 April 2026 | 09:00 - 10:00 | Jasmin Kahriman | Opening Session | [YouTube](url) |
```
